# The Economy · wildcards · gems · the grind

a concept of the MTG (MTG Arena) game-world — emergence: electrical. moniker ⟦The Economy:MTG:020d49⟧

**who —** The Economy — Arena's free-to-play system of gold, gems, packs, and the all-important wildcards that craft any card.
**what —** The pay-to-FAST engine: money accelerates a collection rather than buying wins, with draft as the great skill-equaliser.
**where —** In the store and the reward track, behind every deck you want to build.
**why —** Because a free game still has to make money, and Arena's design nudges the wallet without quite selling the win.
**how —** By packs and wildcards, daily quests and ranked rewards, and the constant pull between grinding and paying.

**the seal —** I am pay-to-fast, not pay-to-win — money buys you the collection sooner, but draft will still humble you on pure skill.

